Durban businesswoman Sandra Moonsamy has been missing since May. JOHANNESBURG - Missing Durban businesswoman Sandra Moonsamy has been found alive and in chains in a house in Emalahleni, Mpumalanga. The Hawks confirmed Moonsamy was found unharmed and is currently being checked at a hospital. READ: Bad weather hampering search for missing Herolds Bay girl Four people have been arrested in connection with the disappearance and firearms were recovered from the property she was held. Moonsamy was taken from her vehicle in Pinetown in May.